v1.30.4 - SECURITY: restore now drains the listener + fails loud (S-5, S-12)

S-5: v1.28 restore ran pg_restore --clean --if-exists against a live DB
while the backend was still serving traffic AND schedulers were still
ticking. A request or scheduler tick could deadlock against a table
pg_restore was about to drop.

S-12: pg_restore exit code 1 was reported as success when stderr happened
not to contain /ERROR:/i. Admins could see "Restore complete" over a
half-restored database.

Fix:
- New lib/maintenance.ts + middleware/maintenance.ts. An InstanceSetting
  key system.maintenanceMode flips on; an onRequest hook 503s every
  route except /health and /api/health. 1s in-process cache so the
  flood of in-flight requests doesn't hammer the pool. Retry-After: 30.
- New lib/lifecycle.ts: app.lifecycle.stopBackground() stops every
  scheduler; app.lifecycle.processExit(code) is process.exit in prod,
  no-op in tests.
- server.ts clears the maintenance flag AFTER listen() succeeds (so a
  backend that crashed mid-boot doesn't lift the gate prematurely).
- routes/backups.ts POST /:filename/restore orchestrates:
  1. setMaintenance + reset cache
  2. stopBackground
  3. svc.restoreBackup
  4a. success - respond 200 then setTimeout(processExit, 250) so body
      flushes; compose restart picks up the restored schema and the
      fresh boot clears the flag
  4b. failure - clearMaintenance; rethrow AppError unchanged so 404
      from missing dump stays 404; non-AppError becomes 400 with
      pg_restore stderr verbatim
- backupsService.restoreBackup adds --exit-on-error and treats ANY
  non-zero exit as failure. Removes the regex-over-stderr heuristic.
  Full stderr surfaces in the 400 body so admins see pg_restore's
  complaint, not a vague generic.
- app.ts adds GET /api/health (public counterpart to the internal
  /health). Both are exempt from the maintenance gate.

6 new tests in backups.test.ts: /api/health and /health stay 200 under
maintenance; normal API returns 503 with structured Retry-After + reason
+ since; cache reset between tests; non-admin restore still 403; corrupt
dump produces 400 with pg_restore stderr; maintenance flag is cleared on
failure.

Phase boundary: failed restore leaves schedulers stopped (DB is in
unknown shape - operator runs docker compose restart backend). Does not
use --single-transaction because CREATE EXTENSION isn't always
transactional. In-flight requests get one last query each (no forceful
app.close before pg_restore) - invisible on small instances, tracked.

Verified: tsc clean. backups.test.ts 13/13. Full suite 287 passed,
5 skipped (LDAP). BACKUP.md + UPGRADE.md describe the new maintenance
window.